{"legislative_session": "2026", "identifier": "SB384", "title": "RELATING TO VICTIM RESTITUTION.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Negligent Homicide in the First Degree", "Victim Restitution"], "abstracts": [{"note": "description", "abstract": "Requires, when a defendant is convicted of negligent homicide in the first degree for causing the death of another while driving under the influence of drugs or alcohol, that victim restitution shall include financial support to raise the decedent's surviving minor children until each child reaches the age of eighteen, or until the age of twenty-three for any child who enrolls full-time in a college, university, vocational school, or trade school, in an amount to be determined by the court and to be paid to the person responsible for raising the children.  Effective 7/1/2050.  (SD1)"}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [], "actions": [{"description": "Carried over to 2026 Regular Session.", "date": "2025-12-08", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"legislature\"}", "classification": ["carried-over"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Report adopted; Passed Second Reading, as amended (SD 1) and referred to JDC.", "date": "2025-02-11", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["reading-2", "referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Judiciary", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "Reported from TCA (Stand. Com. Rep. No. 245) with recommendation of passage on Second Reading, as amended (SD 1) and referral to JDC.", "date": "2025-02-11", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "The committee(s) on  TCA recommend(s) that the measure be PASSED, WITH AMENDMENTS.  The votes in TCA were as follows: 4 Aye(s): Senator(s) Lee, C., Elefante, Kanuha, DeCorte; Aye(s) with reservations: none ; 0 N